Get a document term matrix from abstracts

get_dtm.Rd

Get a document term matrix from abstracts

Usage

get_dtm(abstracts, vocabulary, tf_idf = TRUE)

Arguments

abstracts

Could be an object of class abstracts (created via get_abstracts function) or a charactervector with abstracts

vocabulary

A vocabulary created with the get_vocabulary function, from an abstracts object

tf_idf

logical. If it is true returns dtm weighted with tf idf. Otherwise return binary dtm matrix

Value

Returns a document term matrix. Each row is a document, each term is a matrix from vocabulary

Examples

abstracts <- get_abstracts(lacsSample)
vocabulary <- get_vocabulary(abstracts, term_count = 10)
get_dtm(abstracts, vocabulary, tf_idf = FALSE)
